honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class SerialPortConfiguration_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.SerialPortConfiguration_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SerialPortConfiguration_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the Serial Port Configuration data from an KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    SPABSerial Port A Baud Rate
    SPApSerial Port A Parity
    SPAPSerial Port A Handshaking
    SPASSerial Port A Stop Bit
    SPADSerial Port A Data Bits
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • SerialPortConfiguration_DPL

        public SerialPortConfiguration_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
